
[1]felicitate

   FELIC'ITATE, v.t. [L. felicito, from felix, happy.]

   1. To make very happy.

   What a glorious entertainment and pleasure would fill and felicitate
   his spirit, if he could grasp all in a single survey.

   More generally,

   2. To congratulate; to express joy or pleasure to. We felicitate our
   friends on the acquisition of good, or an escape from evil.

                      FELIC'ITATE, a. Made very happy.
